FBIS3-21902 "jptdd012__l94027" JPRS-TDD-94-012-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 18 March 1994 LATIN AMERICA COLOMBIA Prosecutor General Describes U.S. as `Thin-Skinned' on Drug Issues PA1803014494 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 18 Mar 94 PA1803014494 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 1 Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Report by Alvaro Ayala; from the "24 Hours Newscast"] [Text] Prosecutor General Gustavo de Greiff has not let recent statements by U.S. Attorney General Janet Reno upset him. Today he indicated that the United States is too thin-skinned when it comes to legalizing drugs. The prosecutor general said that U.S. diplomatic officials visited his office and that he had answered U.S. Attorney General Janet Reno. [Begin recording] De Greiff: No, no, it was not a matter of them providing support. It was just to exchange opinions. Unidentified reporter: Mr. Prosecutor, one last question. It would seem that your WASHINGTON POST article has caused quite a frenzy in the United States. De Greiff: That is correct. I am very sorry that this has been the case. It would seem that the Americans are very thin-skinned. [end recording]
